    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Your backend framework wants to evaluate what's inside the js part of the code because it uses the same `{{ }}` for variables. One way to get around that is to use a function instead of a string template. Here is an example based on yours:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n\tcontainer: '#hits',\r\n\ttemplates: {\r\n\t    empty: 'No results',\r\n\t    item: function(hit){ return hit.name; }\r\n\t},\r\n\thitsPerPage: 6,\r\n\tcssClasses: {\r\n\t    root: 'row',\r\n\t    item: 'col-lg-3 col-md-4 col-sm-6'\r\n\t}\r\n    })\r\n);\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2017-09-08T16:17:58Z",
